      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For this AC circuit, you need to find the total impedance ($Z$) first, which is the combination of the resistance ($R$) and the inductive reactance ($X_L$). You can calculate this using the formula $Z = \\sqrt{R^2 + X_L^2}$. With $R = 50\\ \\Omega$ and $X_L = 30\\ \\Omega$, the impedance will be $\\sqrt{50^2 + 30^2} = \\sqrt{2500 + 900} = \\sqrt{3400} \\approx 58.31\\ \\Omega$.\n\nThen, to find the current ($I$), you use Ohm's Law for AC circuits: $I = V_{\\text{rms}} / Z$. Plugging in your values, $I = 120\\ \\text{V} / 58.31\\ \\Omega \\approx 2.06\\ \\text{A}$. So, the total impedance is about $58.31\\ \\Omega$, and the current flowing through the circuit is approximately $2.06\\ \\text{A}$.\n\nIt's",
